# Documentation AI Index and Organization Rules

**Purpose:** Ensure AI agents always load the documentation index first and follow proper documentation organization.

## Context Rules

### Always Include (High Priority)

These files must be included when working with documentation:

1. **`docs/00-ai-index/README.md`** - MANDATORY: AI documentation index with load order and save rules
2. **`docs/20-dev-standards/DOCUMENTATION_GUIDE.md`** - Where to save different document types
3. **`docs/10-system/bmm-brownfield-architecture.md`** - Complete system reference (96 tables, 44 routers, 1,778 tests)

### Prefer Include (Medium Priority)

Load these as needed for specific tasks:

- `docs/30-reference/**` - API, database, config, security references
- `docs/40-guides/**` - Integration guides and specialized documentation
- `docs/50-operations/**` - Deployment and operational procedures

### Exclude from Default Context

These directories are excluded to reduce noise:

- `docs/70-research/**` - Research projects (pricing, market analysis) - load explicitly when needed
- `**/.archive/**` - Old CRM app reference (project root only) - NEVER modify
- `docs/audit/**` - Historical audit reports - reference only

