## Documentation Creation Guardrails

### Before Creating ANY Documentation

**MANDATORY CHECKLIST:**

1. ✅ Read `docs/00-ai-index/README.md` first
2. ✅ Check `docs/20-dev-standards/DOCUMENTATION_GUIDE.md` for correct location
3. ✅ Verify content doesn't already exist in `bmm-brownfield-architecture.md` or `coding-standards.md`
4. ✅ Confirm correct numbered bucket (10/20/30/40/50/60/70/90)

### Prohibited Actions

**DO NOT:**
- ❌ Create files in `docs/` root (max 7 core files allowed)
- ❌ Create stub/placeholder files (<500 words) unless in `60-active-planning/` with phase owner
- ❌ Create duplicate documentation for existing content
- ❌ Create subdirectories for single files
- ❌ Add files to `.archive/` (old CRM app reference only - project root)

### Required Actions

**ALWAYS:**
- ✅ Check `DOCUMENTATION_GUIDE.md` before creating any documentation
- ✅ Use numbered taxonomy (00/10/20/30/40/50/60/70/90) for organization
- ✅ Place active planning in `60-active-planning/{category}/`
- ✅ Place completed phases in `90-completed/{phase-name}/`
- ✅ Ask user if unsure about location or if creating new category

